{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cn9ndhQNcfEd7xGaMQRh3e","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Visual Testing Setup - Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the visual testing infrastructure in the project. Here's what exists:\n\n### 1. Visual Test Files Location\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/`\n\nTwo main test files:\n- `routes.spec.ts` — Tests route baselines (13 routes)\n- `states.spec.ts` — Tests state variants (wallet connected/disconnected, empty states, navigation flows)\n\n### 2. Test Pattern & Screenshot Mechanism\n\n**How screenshots are taken**:\n- Uses Playwright's `toHaveScreenshot()` API\n- Full page screenshots with `fullPage: true`\n- Default max pixel diff ratio: `0.015` (1.5%) — allows 3% for profile/avatar (SVG sub-pixel variance)\n\n**Test structure example**:\n```typescript\ntest(\"home page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"home.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n**Routes tested** (routes.spec.ts):\n- `/` (home)\n- `/coinflip`, `/lord-of-rngs`, `/close-call`, `/crash`, `/game-of-trades`\n- `/close-call/abc123` (round page with dynamic ID)\n- `/profile`, `/quests`, `/loot`, `/fairness`, `/leaderboard`\n- `/nonexistent` (404 page)\n\n**State variants tested** (states.spec.ts):\n- Home page: disconnected vs connected wallet\n- Profile page: connected wallet + transactions empty state\n- Lord of RNGs: lobby (disconnected) → round selected → back to lobby → connected sidebar\n- Close Call: disconnected vs connected\n- Coinflip: disconnected vs connected + error toast positioning\n\n### 3. Custom Fixture: `stablePage`\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n\nThe `stablePage` fixture provides **deterministic visual testing** by:\n\n1. **Deterministic randomness**: Seeds `Math.random()` and `crypto.getRandomValues()` using Mulberry32 PRNG (seed = 42)\n   - Makes avatar SVGs, wallet addresses, and UUIDs reproducible across test runs\n   \n2. **Frozen time**: `Date.now()` locked to `1767225600000` (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n   \n3. **Animation elimination**: Injects CSS to disable all transitions/animations + pauses SVG SMIL animations\n   ```css\n   animation-duration: 0s !important;\n   transition-duration: 0s !important;\n   scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n   svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n   ```\n   \n4. **Network & font readiness**: \n   - Waits for `networkidle` on every `goto()`\n   - Waits for `document.fonts.ready`\n   - 300ms settle time after navigation\n   \n5. **Console error filtering**: Collects console errors but ignores noise patterns:\n   - `401/403/429` (auth/rate limit in mock mode)\n   - `favicon`, `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED`, `Failed to fetch`, `NetworkError`\n   - **Fails the test if any real console errors are found**\n\n### 4. Baseline Storage & Comparison\n\n**Snapshot directory structure**:\n```\napps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/\n├── routes.spec.ts/\n│   ├── home.png\n│   ├── coinflip.png\n│   ├── profile.png\n│   └── ... (13 baseline images)\n└── states.spec.ts/\n    ├── home-disconnected.png\n    ├── home-connected.png\n    ├── coinflip-error-toast-position.png\n    └── ... (15+ baseline images)\n```\n\n**How comparison works**:\n- Playwright compares actual screenshot against baseline\n- Default tolerance: **1.5% pixel diff** (configurable per-test with `maxDiffPixelRatio`)\n- Profile & avatar tests use **3% tolerance** due to SVG sub-pixel rendering variance\n- If diff exceeds threshold, test fails with visual diff report\n\n### 5. Playwright Configuration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\n{\n  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n  testMatch: \"visual/**/*.spec.ts\",  // Only visual/ directory\n  workers: 1,                        // Serial execution (determinism)\n  retries: 0,\n  snapshot: {\n    maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015,       // 1.5% default\n  },\n  use: {\n    baseURL: \"http://127.0.0.1:3000\",\n    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },  // Fixed desktop size\n    screenshot: \"off\",\n    trace: \"off\",\n  },\n  webServer: {\n    command: \"npx vite --port 3000\",\n    env: {\n      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\",        // Runs in mock/dev mode (no backend)\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n**Additional configs**:\n- `playwright.local.config.ts` — for local E2E tests\n- `playwright.devnet.config.ts` — for devnet tests\n- `playwright.real.config.ts` — for real/prod-like tests\n\n### 6. NPM Scripts\n\n**Root package.json** (`sources/rng-utopia/`):\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual --env-mode=loose\"\n```\n\n**App-level package.json** (`sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`):\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\"\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\n**Usage**:\n- Run from root: `pnpm test:visual` → Runs all visual tests\n- Run from app: `cd apps/platform && pnpm test:visual`\n- Update baselines: `pnpm test:visual:update` (when intentional visual changes are made)\n\n### 7. Key Design Patterns\n\n**Wallet state management**:\n- Tests clear localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`) to reset wallet state\n- Then either capture disconnected state OR click wallet button + wait for `.rng-wallet-button--connected`\n\n**Timing & stability**:\n- Class selectors used for waitFor (e.g., `.lotr-tier-lobby`, `.profile-page__tab`)\n- Explicit `waitForSelector()` after interactions\n- 300ms settle time before screenshot to allow final paints\n\n**Error toast testing**:\n- One test programmatically injects an error toast DOM element at runtime\n- Captures its position relative to the page layout\n\n**State-specific tolerance**:\n- Profile/avatar: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.03` (3%) — SVG avatars have sub-pixel variance\n- Most others: default 1.5%\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe visual testing setup is **production-grade**:\n- **Two-file pattern**: routes (13 static pages) + states (15+ interactive flows)\n- **Deterministic fixture**: seeded RNG + frozen time + animation freeze ensures pixel-perfect reproducibility\n- **Smart baseline management**: snapshots stored per-test-file in `__snapshots__/` following Playwright convention\n- **Automated comparison**: 1.5% tolerance by default, tolerant of rendering variance\n- **Integration with dev loop**: `--update-snapshots` flag for intentional changes; runs in mock mode with Vite\n- **Console error detection**: fails on unexpected errors, ignores auth/network noise in mock mode\n\nFiles to reference:\n- Visual test code: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- Fixture logic: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- Playwright config: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n- Baselines: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abe52e5d28d63b2f2 (use SendMessage with to: 'abe52e5d28d63b2f2' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51329\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 127171</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90f4afdf-f404-4516-a077-3e53d0f561c2","uuid":"01458283-f8e7-4435-bf36-133a62bfb360","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:22:13.781Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the visual testing setup in this project. I need to understand:\n1. What visual tests exist in `e2e/visual/` under `sources/rng-utopia/`\n2. The pattern used for visual tests (how they take screenshots, how routes are tested)\n3. How baselines are stored and compared\n4. The test:visual and test:visual:update scripts in package.json\n\nCheck:\n- `sources/rng-utopia/e2e/visual/` directory\n- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/` directory  \n- Any `**/e2e/visual/**` files\n- package.json scripts for test:visual\n- playwright config for visual tests\n\nBe thorough - check multiple possible locations.","agentId":"abe52e5d28d63b2f2","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Visual Testing Setup - Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the visual testing infrastructure in the project. Here's what exists:\n\n### 1. Visual Test Files Location\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/`\n\nTwo main test files:\n- `routes.spec.ts` — Tests route baselines (13 routes)\n- `states.spec.ts` — Tests state variants (wallet connected/disconnected, empty states, navigation flows)\n\n### 2. Test Pattern & Screenshot Mechanism\n\n**How screenshots are taken**:\n- Uses Playwright's `toHaveScreenshot()` API\n- Full page screenshots with `fullPage: true`\n- Default max pixel diff ratio: `0.015` (1.5%) — allows 3% for profile/avatar (SVG sub-pixel variance)\n\n**Test structure example**:\n```typescript\ntest(\"home page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"home.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n**Routes tested** (routes.spec.ts):\n- `/` (home)\n- `/coinflip`, `/lord-of-rngs`, `/close-call`, `/crash`, `/game-of-trades`\n- `/close-call/abc123` (round page with dynamic ID)\n- `/profile`, `/quests`, `/loot`, `/fairness`, `/leaderboard`\n- `/nonexistent` (404 page)\n\n**State variants tested** (states.spec.ts):\n- Home page: disconnected vs connected wallet\n- Profile page: connected wallet + transactions empty state\n- Lord of RNGs: lobby (disconnected) → round selected → back to lobby → connected sidebar\n- Close Call: disconnected vs connected\n- Coinflip: disconnected vs connected + error toast positioning\n\n### 3. Custom Fixture: `stablePage`\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n\nThe `stablePage` fixture provides **deterministic visual testing** by:\n\n1. **Deterministic randomness**: Seeds `Math.random()` and `crypto.getRandomValues()` using Mulberry32 PRNG (seed = 42)\n   - Makes avatar SVGs, wallet addresses, and UUIDs reproducible across test runs\n   \n2. **Frozen time**: `Date.now()` locked to `1767225600000` (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n   \n3. **Animation elimination**: Injects CSS to disable all transitions/animations + pauses SVG SMIL animations\n   ```css\n   animation-duration: 0s !important;\n   transition-duration: 0s !important;\n   scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n   svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n   ```\n   \n4. **Network & font readiness**: \n   - Waits for `networkidle` on every `goto()`\n   - Waits for `document.fonts.ready`\n   - 300ms settle time after navigation\n   \n5. **Console error filtering**: Collects console errors but ignores noise patterns:\n   - `401/403/429` (auth/rate limit in mock mode)\n   - `favicon`, `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED`, `Failed to fetch`, `NetworkError`\n   - **Fails the test if any real console errors are found**\n\n### 4. Baseline Storage & Comparison\n\n**Snapshot directory structure**:\n```\napps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/\n├── routes.spec.ts/\n│   ├── home.png\n│   ├── coinflip.png\n│   ├── profile.png\n│   └── ... (13 baseline images)\n└── states.spec.ts/\n    ├── home-disconnected.png\n    ├── home-connected.png\n    ├── coinflip-error-toast-position.png\n    └── ... (15+ baseline images)\n```\n\n**How comparison works**:\n- Playwright compares actual screenshot against baseline\n- Default tolerance: **1.5% pixel diff** (configurable per-test with `maxDiffPixelRatio`)\n- Profile & avatar tests use **3% tolerance** due to SVG sub-pixel rendering variance\n- If diff exceeds threshold, test fails with visual diff report\n\n### 5. Playwright Configuration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\n{\n  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n  testMatch: \"visual/**/*.spec.ts\",  // Only visual/ directory\n  workers: 1,                        // Serial execution (determinism)\n  retries: 0,\n  snapshot: {\n    maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015,       // 1.5% default\n  },\n  use: {\n    baseURL: \"http://127.0.0.1:3000\",\n    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },  // Fixed desktop size\n    screenshot: \"off\",\n    trace: \"off\",\n  },\n  webServer: {\n    command: \"npx vite --port 3000\",\n    env: {\n      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\",        // Runs in mock/dev mode (no backend)\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n**Additional configs**:\n- `playwright.local.config.ts` — for local E2E tests\n- `playwright.devnet.config.ts` — for devnet tests\n- `playwright.real.config.ts` — for real/prod-like tests\n\n### 6. NPM Scripts\n\n**Root package.json** (`sources/rng-utopia/`):\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual --env-mode=loose\"\n```\n\n**App-level package.json** (`sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`):\n```\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\"\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\n**Usage**:\n- Run from root: `pnpm test:visual` → Runs all visual tests\n- Run from app: `cd apps/platform && pnpm test:visual`\n- Update baselines: `pnpm test:visual:update` (when intentional visual changes are made)\n\n### 7. Key Design Patterns\n\n**Wallet state management**:\n- Tests clear localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`) to reset wallet state\n- Then either capture disconnected state OR click wallet button + wait for `.rng-wallet-button--connected`\n\n**Timing & stability**:\n- Class selectors used for waitFor (e.g., `.lotr-tier-lobby`, `.profile-page__tab`)\n- Explicit `waitForSelector()` after interactions\n- 300ms settle time before screenshot to allow final paints\n\n**Error toast testing**:\n- One test programmatically injects an error toast DOM element at runtime\n- Captures its position relative to the page layout\n\n**State-specific tolerance**:\n- Profile/avatar: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.03` (3%) — SVG avatars have sub-pixel variance\n- Most others: default 1.5%\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe visual testing setup is **production-grade**:\n- **Two-file pattern**: routes (13 static pages) + states (15+ interactive flows)\n- **Deterministic fixture**: seeded RNG + frozen time + animation freeze ensures pixel-perfect reproducibility\n- **Smart baseline management**: snapshots stored per-test-file in `__snapshots__/` following Playwright convention\n- **Automated comparison**: 1.5% tolerance by default, tolerant of rendering variance\n- **Integration with dev loop**: `--update-snapshots` flag for intentional changes; runs in mock mode with Vite\n- **Console error detection**: fails on unexpected errors, ignores auth/network noise in mock mode\n\nFiles to reference:\n- Visual test code: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- Fixture logic: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- Playwright config: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n- Baselines: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`"}],"totalDurationMs":127171,"totalTokens":51329,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":475,"cache_read_input_tokens":48753,"output_tokens":2101,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":475},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
