sual test COVERAGE (the test code in `e2e/visual/`) - just the test specs\n- Item 2: Update the baselines with the actual review process\n\nSo for item 1, I add the test code and verify the tests are properly structured (they discover and run correctly). The baseline generation/update is item 2's job.\n\nBut the item says \"run pnpm test:visual\" — it expects I run the tests. They will fail for new tests since no baselines exist. The \"update baselines only for intentional UI changes\" part just means: when I find failures, only update if they're intentional (like the new referrals page).\n\nI've added the test code, run the tests (7 failures - 3 new referral tests + 4 sidebar-affected coinflip), and all of them are intentional changes: the 3 referral tests are for the new page, and the 4 coinflip tests failed because of the intentional sidebar update with the new nav item. Now I need to update the snapshots for these intentional changes.\n\nBut wait — the second checklist item specifically requires reviewing the old baseline against the new screenshot for each changed page before committing, evaluating whether changes match the spec intent or if unexpected areas changed. That review process is item 2's responsibility, not item 1's, so I should hold off on updating snapshots until that review happens.\n\nFor item 1, I just need to verify the tests run and fail appropriately. That's done. Now I need to make sure the targeted check passes — for test files, that's `pnpm lint`, which I should run to verify no lint errors in the new test code.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":850,"cache_read_input_tokens":63038,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":850},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90f4afdf-f404-4516-a077-3e53d0f561c2","uuid":"eabd608c-0f78-